## Committing Code

Follow conventional commit format:

```bash
git commit -m "feat: DSTEW-1234 Add new feature"
git commit -m "fix: DSTEW-5678 Fix bug"
git commit -m "docs: Update README"
```

Valid types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`, `infra`

